# ABOUTME: Per-CVE Trivy suppressions with written justification, per ADR-012 /
# ABOUTME: dev_plan/10_operations_runbook.md §16. Review every entry quarterly.
#
# Policy: security.yml sets `ignore-unfixed: false` so unfixed CRITICAL/HIGH
# CVEs fail the scan by default. To suppress a CVE here, you MUST include:
#   1. The affected package(s) and Debian tracker link.
#   2. Whether the vulnerable code path is reachable from our runtime.
#   3. A review trigger (base-image bump, upstream patch, etc.).
# Blanket suppressions are not allowed.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CVE-2023-45853 — CRITICAL — zlib1g 1:1.2.13 MiniZip integer overflow
# Packages: zlib1g (base image python:3.12.7-slim → Debian 12 bookworm)
# Tracker:  https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2023-45853
# Stance:   Debian marks this no-DSA / end-of-life because the vulnerable
#           MiniZip code lives in zlib's contrib/ subdirectory and is NOT
#           compiled into the distro package. Our application does not
#           invoke MiniZip directly (no zip-handling code path).
# Review:   Drop this entry when we bump base to Debian 13 (trixie) — planned
#           as a Phase 2 follow-up since the trixie image ships newer zlib.
CVE-2023-45853

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CVE-2025-69720 — HIGH — ncurses 6.4-4 memory safety
# Packages: ncurses-bin, ncurses-base, libtinfo6, libncursesw6
# Tracker:  https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2025-69720
# Stance:   Unfixed in Debian 12 bookworm; Debian 12 LTS backport pending.
#           The API container runs uvicorn non-interactively — no stdin TTY,
#           no readline usage in app code (verified: no `import readline` or
#           `import curses` in api/). Library is present purely as a
#           transitive dependency of Python's build (not consumed at
#           runtime).
# Review:   Re-evaluate on Debian 12 LTS backport or trixie upgrade.
CVE-2025-69720

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CVE-2026-29111 — HIGH — systemd 252.31-1~deb12u1
# Packages: libsystemd0, libudev1
# Tracker:  https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-29111
# Stance:   Unfixed in Debian 12 bookworm. Our container does not run
#           systemd and app code does not link libsystemd at runtime. These
#           libraries are transitive deps of other base-image packages only.
# Review:   Re-evaluate on Debian 12 LTS backport or trixie upgrade.
CVE-2026-29111

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CVE-2026-0861 — HIGH — glibc 2.36 integer overflow in memalign
# Packages: libc-bin, libc6
# Tracker:  https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-0861
# Stance:   Unfixed in Debian 12. glibc is required by Python; the vulnerable
#           code path is `memalign()` with attacker-controlled size values.
#           Python's stdlib does not expose memalign, and none of our deps
#           (bcrypt, cryptography, asyncpg) call it directly. No user input
#           reaches a memalign call at runtime.
# Review:   Re-evaluate on Debian 12 LTS backport or trixie upgrade.
CVE-2026-0861

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CVE-2025-7458 — CRITICAL — sqlite3 integer overflow
# Packages: libsqlite3-0
# Tracker:  https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2025-7458
# Stance:   Application uses Postgres via asyncpg; Python stdlib `sqlite3`
#           is not imported anywhere in api/ (verified:
#           `grep -r "import sqlite3" api/` = 0 hits). The library ships
#           with CPython but is never loaded. apt-get upgrade brings us to
#           libsqlite3-0 3.40.1-2+deb12u2 but Trivy marks that version as
#           still affected; awaiting a Debian patch or trixie upgrade.
# Review:   Re-evaluate on next base-image / sqlite version bump.
CVE-2025-7458
